# Kerry Hanson Portfolio — Cursor Rules

## Project overview

Personal UX designer portfolio built with React 19, Vite 7, React Router, Tailwind CSS v4, and Lucide React. Deployed on Vercel.

## Stack and conventions

- Use JavaScript (`.jsx` / `.js`), not TypeScript.
- Use Tailwind utility classes plus existing `theme-*` CSS utilities from `src/index.css`.
- Use Lucide React for icons. Brand icons (e.g. LinkedIn) are not available in lucide-react 1.x — use generic icons like `Link2`.
- Prefer functional components and hooks. Keep components focused and colocated under `src/components/`, pages under `src/pages/`.

## Theming

- Four themes: `light`, `soft`, `dusk`, `dark` — defined via `[data-theme]` CSS variables in `src/index.css`.
- Always use theme-aware classes (`theme-text`, `theme-surface`, `theme-accent`, `theme-border`, etc.) instead of hardcoded colors so all themes stay in sync.
- Theme state lives in `src/context/ThemeContext.jsx` and persists to `localStorage`.

## Content and data

- Profile/resume content: `src/data/profile.js`
- Project case studies: `src/data/projects.js` — add optional `image`, `imageAlt`, `imageWidth`, `imageHeight` for real screenshots
- Hero slider config: `src/config/heroVisual.js` — set `HERO_VISUAL_MODE` to `'placeholder'` or `'flow-diagram'`; configure slide images in `HERO_SLIDES`
- Static assets go in `public/` (e.g. `public/images/`)

## UI patterns

- Use `PlaceholderImage` for image slots without assets yet; use `ProjectImage` for project cards/pages (handles image vs placeholder).
- Hover effects on cards only for clickable links (`a.theme-card`), not static content cards.
- Interactive menus (theme selector, mobile nav) must work on tap — use click/toggle, not hover-only.
- Avoid layout shift: reserve fixed space for elements that change size on active/hover states.

## Hero slider

- Research / Design / Impact tabs in `HeroFlowDiagram.jsx` control slide pagination.
- Auto-cycles every 10 seconds; timer resets on manual navigation.
- Pagination icons: `SquareUserRound`, `LayoutDashboard`, `Rocket`.

## Scope and quality

- Minimize diff scope — only change what the task requires.
- Match existing naming, file structure, and styling patterns.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly asked.
- Run `npm run build` to verify changes compile before finishing.

## Code & Component Quality

- Write clean, modular, and reusable components. Avoid monolithic files.
- Use semantic HTML tags exclusively (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`) instead of generic nested `<div>` wrappers.
- Optimize images using lazy loading and responsive source sets.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.2) Mandate

- Every interactive element must have a clear `:focus-visible` state.
- All icons (Lucide) must include `aria-hidden="true"` if decorative, or explicit labels if functional.
- Ensure full keyboard navigation support for custom interactive components or carousels.
- Include proper `aria-*` attributes for dynamic UI states (e.g., mobile menu toggle).

## Deployment

- Vercel serves the Vite build from `dist/`.
- `vercel.json` includes SPA rewrites for client-side routing — preserve when editing config.
